<section>
    <h2>Description</h2>
    <p>The <code>&lt;shortcuts-wc&gt;</code> component provides a keyboard shortcuts help overlay, similar to GitHub's <kbd>?</kbd> shortcut or Gmail's shortcut reference. Place it once in your layout and press <kbd>?</kbd> to see all currently bound keyboard shortcuts grouped by source.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Basic Usage</h2>
    <p>Drop <code>&lt;shortcuts-wc&gt;</code> anywhere on the page. It renders nothing visible &mdash; it only binds the <kbd>?</kbd> hotkey. Press <kbd>?</kbd> on this page to try it (it's already included in the layout).</p>
    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Basic usage">{{ basicCode | safe }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>How It Works</h2>
    <p>When opened, the overlay reads from the <strong>command registry</strong> (<code>window.__commandRegistry</code>) to find all registered commands that have a <code>data-shortcut</code> attribute. Shortcuts are displayed grouped by their <code>data-command-group</code>.</p>
    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="With commands">{{ withCommandsCode | safe }}</code-block>
  </section>

